SEOUL, South Korea A former top intelligence official killed himself just days after being questioned about his involvement in a South Korean wiretapping scandal, police said Monday Lee Soo-il, 63, who worked as deputy chief of the National Intelligence Service from 2001 to 2003, was found dead by hanging Sunday evening at his home in Gwangju, about 330 kilometers (200 miles) south of Seoul, said Chung Yong-min, an officer at the Gwangju Seobu Police Station.
